  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "We call $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ dissociated if $\\sum_{n\\in X}n\\neq \\sum_{m\\in Y}m$ for all finite $X,Y\\subset A$ with $X\\neq Y$. \n\nLet $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ be an infinite set. We call $A$ proportionately dissociated if every finite $B\\subset A$ contains a dissociated set of size $\\gg \\lvert B\\rvert$.\n\nIs every proportionately dissociated set the union of a finite number of dissociated sets?",
    "intended_statement_status": "source_text_pending_theorem_level_audit",
